"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-world-europe-paris-2024-hopes-to-be-model-for-lower-carbon-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get ST's newsletters delivered to your inbox  Paris 2024 initially set an emissions target equivalent to 1.58 million tonnes of carbon dioxide, but that ambition has been lowered to around 1.75 million tonnes  PHOTO: AFP  PublishedMar 14, 2024, 11:05 AM  UpdatedMar 25, 2024, 12:24 PM  PARIS-The 2024 Paris Olympics will use renewable energy, serve lots of vegetarian meals and heavily restrict plastic bottles, but can an event involving so much construction and international travel ever be environmentally sustainable?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.666226995056164e-19, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1296065154577784e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After an extravagant Fifa football World Cup in Qatar in 2022 that featured air-conditioned stadiums, the Paris Games are hoping to present a more sober model for global sports events.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999999835245036, \"rank\": 1.6475679395150927e-08, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope Paris 2024's efforts to reduce its impacts can demonstrate that it is possible to do things differently,\\\" Ms Georgina Grenon, director of environmental excellence for the organising committee, told AFP in a recent interview.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1296065154577784e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1111, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999977126208, \"rank\": 2.2873403430176173e-09, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the main differences will be in the overall carbon emissions, with organisers aiming for half of the amount generated by the 2012 Olympics in London and the 2016 edition in Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.99999992928588, \"rank\": 6.805001939701386e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7459110151451533e-17, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 initially set a target equivalent to 1.58 million tonnes of carbon dioxide, but that ambition has been lowered to around 1.75 million tonnes.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1296065154577784e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Something we are uncertain of today is the (carbon impact of) spectators,\\\" said Ms Grenon when asked if the latest target can be met.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the key factors will be the number of heavily polluting plane journeys linked to the Gamesand \\\"we have not yet sold all the tickets\\\", she added.\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An external consulting firm will be tasked with auditing the impact of travel, construction, catering and sports equipment, with final figures set to be published in October.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The key to reducing Paris' carbon footprint was contained in the city's original bid.\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.988028362711494e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers promised to use either existing or temporary venues for 95 per cent of the sports events, meaning they could avoid building new stadiums from scratch.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The only major new-build projects have been an aquatics centre, a mid-sized venue in Paris for badminton and gymnastics, and the athletes' village in the deprived Paris suburb of Seine-Saint-Denis.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2290, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.988028362711494e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.988028362711494e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contractors for the village had to agree to reduce emissions resulting from their buildings by 30 per cent compared with standard construction, meaning many of them experimented with low-carbon concrete and wood.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other changes included connecting up all the sports venues to the electricity mains supply, meaning stadium operators do not rely on diesel generators for power.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To give you an idea of the volume of diesel for the London Games, there were 4 million litres burned just for electricity purposes,\\\" said Ms Grenon.\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coca-Cola - a top Olympics sponsor - has agreed to install 700 newly designed drink fountains at Olympic venues, meaning that around 50 per cent of soft drinks will be served without a plastic bottle.\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, meals at sports venues will be 60 per cent vegetarian.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Recycling and reuse clauses were routinely written into equipment supplier contracts.\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the energy supplied to the Games by national energy group EDF will be from renewable sources.\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where Games organisers still face an uphill battle to convince observers is their policy on compensating for their emissions - something known as \\\"carbon offsetting\\\".\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if they meet their emissions target of 1.75 million tonnes, it would be the equivalent of the annual carbon footprint of a French town of 200,000 people.\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3687, \"end\": 3698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"score\": 0.999967104937146, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French town\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They initially claimed that Paris 2024 would be \\\"carbon-positive\\\", meaning that the organising committee would invest in projects such as tree-planting that would capture more carbon dioxide over their lifetimes than the Games would emit.\", \"from\": 3719, \"to\": 3957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3747, \"end\": 3757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1296065154577784e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This target has also been revised downwards - the Games now aim to be \\\"carbon-neutral\\\" - and a tender for an offsetting project in France was cancelled in late2023for budget reasons, Ms Grenon said.\", \"from\": 3959, \"to\": 4157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4090, \"end\": 4096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994121683993358, \"rank\": 0.000533196424873429, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Offsetting remains controversial because of doubts about the environmental benefits of many schemes, as well as the lack of independent oversight.\", \"from\": 4159, \"to\": 4305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some critics see its main role as supplying clean consciences for polluters.\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been a lot of criticism about some certification methodologies, about some countries being more serious than others, so this is why we chose projects that from the onset were particularly serious,\\\" Ms Grenon countered.\", \"from\": 4384, \"to\": 4612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A forestry project in France has state certification - \\\"label bas carbone\\\" - and the international ones have been \\\"audited to death\\\" and will be revealed to the media \\\"soon\\\", Ms Grenon promised.\", \"from\": 4614, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4636, \"end\": 4642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994121683993358, \"rank\": 0.000533196424873429, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics have faced protests by environmental groups since the 1980s.\", \"from\": 4810, \"to\": 4883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some oppose it outright, saying any social benefits are outweighed by the ecological costs, while others believe the concept simply needs to be re-thought.\", \"from\": 4885, \"to\": 5040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One group of researchers suggested in the Nature Sustainability journal in 2021 that the event be scaled down, held in the same locations, and with far fewer international travellers.\", \"from\": 5042, \"to\": 5225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5084, \"end\": 5105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_Nature_Research_journals\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nature Sustainability\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_Nature_Research_journals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_Nature_Research_journals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is something around sports and around the Olympic Games that is unique, the emotions, the peace message,\\\" Ms Grenon argued.\", \"from\": 5227, \"to\": 5357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The future starts with the present, and the present starts by understanding your impact, and trying to do as much as you can to reduce it,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5359, \"to\": 5509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's been our credo since the very beginning.\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"AFP  Olympics 2024  Environmental issues  Sustainability  Renewable energy  Vegetarian food  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 5559, \"to\": 5768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5602, \"end\": 5616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sustainability\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.18351278107367e-62, \"text\": \"Sustainability\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sustainability\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sustainability\"}, {\"begin\": 5618, \"end\": 5634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renewable_energy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.486876652246668e-59, \"text\": \"Renewable energy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renewable_energy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renewable_energy\"}, {\"begin\": 5685, \"end\": 5693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 5769, \"to\": 5783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 5785, \"to\": 5802, \"entities\": []}]}"